Hi Karlo,

I hope you're doing well.

Upon reviewing, yes — MonsterInsights can help track PDF downloads. It has automatic file download tracking built-in, works seamlessly with GA4, and doesn’t require any coding.
Alternatively, you can also track this directly in GA4 by setting up a custom event, but that would require some manual configuration or using Google Tag Manager.

Hi Joel

I have an enquiry re: Google Analytics. I'm trying to get stats on page views on some PDF documents on our website. Here are some of them:
https://www.msaustralia.org.au/wp-content/uploads/rediplan.pdf
https://www.msaustralia.org.au/wp-content/uploads/crisis-toolkit-preparedness.pdf

I did not create any GA Event. And I just noticed that our MonsterInsight license is already expired, thus probably deactivated.

Is there a way to back track views for pdf using our current GA set up? If not, can we renew our MonsterInsight license? I might be wrong, but this plugin would have stats reporting for pdf downloads, correct?

Would like to hear your recommendations.

Thanks
Karlo
